          <div>
          <head>Stone.</head>
            <p><hi rend="italic">Type of monument:</hi> Panel. 
            <hi rend="italic">Material:</hi> Limestone. 
              <hi rend="italic">Description and condition:</hi> Panel in the shape of mirror - circle with a handle; on the polished obverse face – a rectangular depression crowned with three triangular extensions, and within the depression - one large cross with arms ending in serifs, and two smaller crosses of identical shape above the horizontal and to the left and right of the vertical arms of the central cross; the reverse side is polished and bears a six-petal rosette carved by a different hand than the obverse.
              <hi rend="italic">Dimensions:</hi> H. 0.25, W. 0.21, Th. 0.04. 
              <hi rend="italic">Autopsy:</hi> May 1999, August 2001, September 2002, September 2003, September 2004, September 2005, September 2006, September 2007.</p>
            <p>— <hi rend="italic">Find place:</hi> Herakleian peninsula. 
              <hi rend="italic">Find circumstances:</hi> 1928, excavations of K. E. Grinevich. 
              <hi rend="italic">Find context:</hi> Berman’s Gully, settlement, enclosure 8.</p>
            <p><hi rend="italic">Modern location:</hi> Sevastopol, Ukraine.
              <hi rend="italic">Institution and inventory:</hi> National Preserve of Tauric Chersonesos, 30578</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <head>Inscription 1. Text field: </head>
            <p><hi rend="italic">Faces code:</hi> f1. 
              <hi rend="italic">Placement of text:</hi> Left and right of the depression with a relief of three crosses.
              <hi rend="italic">Style of lettering:</hi> Lapidary; on the right side, the letters lean to the right; imitation of the uncial script of manuscript titles; letters vertically elongated. Alpha with a loop, unclosed kappa, mu with a curved horizontal, rho with a triangular loop, cross-haped psi. Ligature eta-nu.
              <hi rend="italic">Letterheights:</hi> 0.005–0.008.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <head>Text:</head>
            <p><hi rend="italic">Origin of text:</hi> Chersonesos. 
              <hi rend="italic">Document type:</hi> Dedication.  
              <hi rend="italic">Date:</hi> 14th cent. 
              <hi rend="italic">Dating criteria:</hi> Visual decoration; language.</p>
            <p><hi rend="italic">Editions:</hi> L1. Shangin 1938, 85-87, no. 14.</p>
            
